{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_012r7iWJqXP38Qm8VAQRpa1g","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `lib/hotels.ts` file looks good. JSON imports with `as Hotel[]` casting could be a TypeScript issue since the JSON doesn't perfectly match the type (all numbers are correctly typed). Let me think...\n\nActually, `hotelsData as Hotel[]` should work fine since all the fields match. The `const hotels: Hotel[] = hotelsData as Hotel[]` means we're directly casting the JSON data to `Hotel[]`. And `const reviews: Review[] = reviewsData as Review[]` does the same for reviews.\n\nOne potential issue: `const hotels: Hotel[] = hotelsData as Hotel[]` - the `hotels` array is a MODULE SINGLETON in Node.js. \n\nWhen we mutate hotel objects by updating `reviewCount` and `averageRating`, those changes persist in the module-level array since it's shared across requests in the same Node.js process. This is actually the desired in-memory behavior, but there's a subtle caching issue with Next.js App Router—GET Route Handlers are cached by default, which could affect how these mutations are exposed.\n\nHowever, in Next.js 15+, GET handlers default to dynamic caching, so they'll always re-fetch. For Server Components like the main page, caching could be an issue, but the MVP handles this gracefully since the `ReviewSection` client component posts new reviews via fetch and updates local state immediately, so new reviews appear in the UI without waiting for server re-renders.\n\nLet me verify the zustand v5 API to make sure the persist middleware still works as expected...\n\nChecking zustand v5 migration...\n\nThe persist middleware setup I wrote should work as-is in v5 — the generic type parameter is still supported. Now I'll move on to writing the README.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1573,"cache_read_input_tokens":119053,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1573},"output_tokens":19,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1a46cfe3-edd5-47d3-88ea-9b5bc1fd0648","uuid":"dde5a302-91cb-40f6-8b91-4e5c00a49c5e","request_id":"req_011CcdTkcL61Rs33hiFkQ4ze"}
