timebox; resets on server restart (documented below) |\n| Testing | Vitest + @testing-library/react | Fast unit tests for pure logic; no Playwright given timebox |\n| Icons | lucide-react | Tree-shakeable, consistent icon set |\n\n### File structure\n\n```\napp/\n  page.tsx                        # Search/results home\n  hotels/[id]/page.tsx            # Hotel details\n  favorites/page.tsx              # Saved hotels\n  checkout/[hotelId]/page.tsx     # Checkout form\n  checkout/confirmation/[bookingId]/page.tsx  # Booking confirmation\n  api/\n    hotels/route.ts               # GET list/search\n    hotels/[id]/route.ts          # GET single hotel\n    hotels/[id]/reviews/route.ts  # GET/POST reviews\n    hotels/[id]/availability/route.ts  # GET availability/price\n    bookings/route.ts             # POST create booking\n    bookings/[id]/route.ts        # GET booking\ncomponents/\n  booking/    # DateGuestPicker, CheckoutForm\n  favorites/  # FavoriteButton\n  hotels/     # HotelCard, PhotoGallery, AmenitiesList\n  reviews/    # ReviewList, ReviewForm\n  search/     # SearchBar, FilterPanel\n  shared/     # EmptyState, ErrorState, LoadingSkeleton, StarRating\ndata/\n  hotels.json   # 10 seed hotels across Paris, Tokyo, London, etc.\n  reviews.json  # 16 seed reviews\nlib/\n  hotels.ts     # Hotel search/filter/sort logic + review mutations\n  bookings.ts   # Booking creation/lookup\n  schemas/      # Zod schemas shared by forms and route handlers\n  stores/       # Zustand favorites store\n  types.ts      # Shared TypeScript interfaces\n  utils/        # Price formatting, date helpers\ntests/\n  filter-hotels.spec.ts  # Hotel search/filter/sort unit tests\n  pricing.spec.ts        # Availability/price calculation tests\n  schemas.spec.ts        # Zod schema validation tests\n.github/workflows/ci.yml  # lint + test + build on push/PR\n```\n\n### Data flow\n\n**Search/results:** URL search params → Server Component reads params → calls `lib/hotels.ts` filter logic → renders `HotelCard` grid. No client state for filters — everything lives in the URL so links are shareable.\n\n**Hotel details:** Server Component fetches hotel + initial reviews → passes to Client Components (`DateGuestPicker`, `ReviewSection`). Availability is fetched client-side on date/guest change via the `/api/hotels/:id/availability` endpoint.\n\n**Reviews:** Initial list rendered server-side. New reviews are posted via `fetch` from `ReviewForm` (client) and prepended to local state immediately — no full page reload.\n\n**Favorites:** Zustand store persisted to `localStorage`. Toggling from any hotel card updates store instantly (optimistic). Favorites page fetches the hotel data for each saved ID on mount.\n\n**Checkout:** Server Component validates availability → passes totals to `CheckoutForm` (client). On submit, posts to `/api/bookings` (mocked payment always succeeds) → redirects to confirmation page.\n\n### Tradeoffs and known limitations\n\n- **In-memory data resets on server restart.** New reviews and bookings are stored in module-level arrays. This is appropriate for a demo; a real app would use a database.\n- **No authentication.** Favorites are per-browser (localStorage). Bookings and reviews are guest-only. Cross-device sync is out of scope.\n- **No map view.** The PRD specified Leaflet, but it was cut due to SSR/bundle complexity and time. Hotels include `lat`/`lng` fields — adding a map is straightforward.\n- **Static hotel data.** Real availability (occupancy, room inventory) is not modeled; `computeAvailability` only validates date range and guest count.\n- **No real payment.** `POST /api/bookings` discards card details and always returns `status: \"confirmed\"`.\n- **Booking persistence.** Because bookings live in memory, navigating directly to `/checkout/confirmation/:id` after a server restart shows a not-found page. This is documented in that page's copy.\n\n## What I would do next\n\n1. **Database:** Replace in-memory arrays with a lightweight DB (SQLite via Drizzle ORM, or PlanetScale for hosted MySQL). Would immediately fix the reset-on-restart limitation.\n2. **Map view:** Add Leaflet + OpenStreetMap tiles. The `lat`/`lng` fields and data model are already in place.\n3. **Auth:** Add NextAuth.js with a magic-link/email provider. Would enable persistent favorites and booking history per user.\n4. **Real payment:** Stripe test-mode integration.\n5. **Review moderation:** Basic profanity filter + admin flagging UI.\n6. **Vercel deploy:** The project is Vercel-ready — add `NEXTAUTH_SECRET` env var and deploy.\n7. **E2E tests:** Playwright happy path (search → details → checkout → confirmation).\n8. **Toast notifications:** `sonner` for favorited/review-submitted/booking-confirmed feedback.\n\n## LLM usage\n\nClaude Code (claude-sonnet-4-6) was used throughout, running as Ralph, an autonomous development agent.\n\n**What it handled:**\n- Scaffolded the entire application: data models, Zod schemas, API route handlers, all React components, pages, and tests in one session.\n- Read the Next.js 16 docs from `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` before writing routing code (caught the `params: Promise<{}>` breaking change vs. earlier Next.js versions).\n- Wrote the PRD (`docs/PRD.md`) before implementation, used it as the spec.\n\n**Approach:**\n- Prompted with the assessment brief → had Claude produce a PRD first, then implement against it.\n- Kept components small and single-responsibility; the LLM naturally produces cleaner code when each prompt has a narrow scope.\n- Reviewed all generated code before committing; corrected a handful of subtle issues (e.g. unused imports, hidden input/react-hook-form interaction).\n\n**Guardrails:**\n- All external URLs in mock data use Unsplash (no API key, public CDN images).\n- No real payment, no real PII stored.\n- Mocked payment card fields are validated client- and server-side to demo the form flow, but stripped before any processing.\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart"